title: Sidewall
provenance: From the house of the Greisheim family, now demolished, which was built by Nahl 1800 at 41 Obere Konigstrasse, Kassel. A store now occupies the site.
description: Horizontal cluster of flowers and leaves is arranged in vertical columns, every other cluster being turned around. Horizontally the repeat is dropped so that the flower clusters interlock. Printed on an irise or rainbow background.
name: Sidewall
